                    <tei:msContents>
                        <tei:summary>
                            <tei:p>This is one of the two kylikes found in the La Penna necropolis in Falerii Veteres. These two kylikes (Vetter 244 a-b; Giacomelli 5 I-II; Bakkum 59-60) are very similar one to each other: they report (quite) the same inscription and they have a portrayal of an erotic scene. Archaeologists have found another kylix that seems like the first two but without inscription on it. Thus, probably the kylikes were produced in a series (see note 5, page 173 <tei:ref target="http://zotero.org/groups/2552746/items/37UB6ZHR"><tei:bibl>Rigobianco 2015</tei:bibl></tei:ref>)</tei:p>
                        </tei:summary>
                    </tei:msContents>
