                        <tei:handDesc>
                            <tei:handNote>
                                <tei:note type="palaeographicNotes">The graphemes used for denoting -r- on carefo and cra have different shape. To explain this graphic difference some scholars have suggested that the two different graphemes could denote different phonemes, respectively [r] and [z]. According to this, the second grapheme was used to represente a not yet completely rhotacized /s/ (see for example <tei:ref target="http://zotero.org/groups/2552746/items/QY9BTP3H"><tei:bibl>Bonfante 1966</tei:bibl></tei:ref>). This suggestion is not accepted anymore and now the difference between the two graphemes for -r- is explained as graphic variants due to an error made during the transcription of the text from a previous copy (see for example <tei:ref target="http://zotero.org/groups/2552746/items/37UB6ZHR"><tei:bibl>Rigobianco 2015</tei:bibl></tei:ref>)</tei:note>
                            </tei:handNote>
                        </tei:handDesc>
